      <FaqItem question="Do I need to pay for tools to get started?" answer="No. ConvertKit, MailerLite, and Mailchimp all have free tiers adequate for the first 500–1,000 subscribers. Carrd and Systeme.io both offer free landing page plans. Organic social media is free. The only paid element — traffic — is optional at the start if you are willing to invest time in organic channels instead." />

      <FaqItem question="What is the difference between lead generation and list building?" answer="List building is the act of growing your email subscriber count. Lead generation is the process of attracting people who match your ideal customer profile and capturing their information systematically. You can build a large list of poorly matched subscribers — that is list building without effective lead generation. Effective lead generation produces a smaller but better-qualified list that converts at a meaningful rate." />

      <FaqItem question="Is lead generation only for B2B companies?" answer="No. Lead generation is used in B2C, B2B, affiliate marketing, e-commerce, local services, and direct-response marketing. The tactics differ by context — B2B uses LinkedIn and direct outreach; affiliate marketers use solo ads and organic social; local businesses use Google Ads and local SEO — but the underlying system is the same across every industry." />

      <FaqItem question="How do I know if my lead magnet is good enough?" answer="A well-matched lead magnet converts 20–40% of landing page visitors into subscribers. Below 10% typically means the offer is not specific enough for your audience, or the landing page copy does not communicate its value clearly. Start by testing the headline — it has the largest single impact on conversion rate. Change one element at a time and measure the result before changing anything else." />

      <FaqItem question="What is the fastest lead generation channel for a complete beginner?" answer="Direct outreach is fastest if you have a warm network and a relevant offer. Paid social ads with $10–20/day can deliver the first lead within 24–48 hours. Solo ads in affiliate niches are similarly fast. Organic social and SEO are slower but cost far less over a 6–12 month horizon. Match your channel choice to your budget and your urgency, not to what sounds most sophisticated." />
    </section>

